---
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Refund Policy"
  description="How refunds, deposits, and cancellations are handled for Designed to Elevate engagements."
  pathname="refund"
  intro="This policy explains how deposits, project payments, and cancellations are handled. Final terms for any specific engagement are set by the signed proposal."
>
  <h2>Deposits</h2>
  <p>
    Most projects require a non-refundable deposit before work begins. This deposit reserves project time and
    covers initial discovery, planning, and onboarding work. The exact deposit amount is outlined in the
    project proposal.
  </p>

  <h2>Project work in progress</h2>
  <p>
    Once a project is underway, fees for work that has already been completed at the time of any cancellation
    request are non-refundable. If a project is paused or cancelled, you will be billed for work performed up
    to that point and any in-progress work will stop.
  </p>

  <h2>Monthly support and consulting</h2>
  <p>
    Ongoing monthly support engagements can be cancelled with reasonable written notice. Fees already paid for
    the current billing period are non-refundable. Pre-paid one-time strategy sessions are refundable up to
    forty-eight (48) hours before the scheduled session; sessions cancelled inside that window or rescheduled
    multiple times may be forfeited at our discretion.
  </p>

  <h2>Chargebacks</h2>
  <p>
    Please contact us first if you have a billing concern. Initiating a chargeback before discussing the issue
    may result in suspension of services and recovery of associated fees. We aim to resolve concerns directly
    and fairly.
  </p>

  <h2>Exceptional cases</h2>
  <p>
    Refunds outside of the cases above are considered on a case-by-case basis. We try to be reasonable. If
    something has gone wrong on our end, we want to know about it and make it right.
  </p>

  <h2>How to request a refund or cancellation</h2>
  <p>
    Email <a href="mailto:bilsonxnc@gmail.com">bilsonxnc@gmail.com</a> with your name, project name, and a brief
    description of the request. We will respond within a reasonable time.
  </p>

  <h2>Updates</h2>
  <p>
    This policy may be updated from time to time. The effective date above reflects the most recent version.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
